Counting only true positives does not account for interference from false positives. In order to meet our minimum counts for detection, our equation must remove false counts (NFalse). The generally accepted procedure for LOD calculations with a 99.7% CI is to assign NTrue only when the counts exceed the background plus three standard deviations of the background (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
