Using this calculation of LOD to optimize an assay has three limitations. First, Equation (1) fails to produce a number with physical meaning when the number of true-positive events (NTrue) is less than the number of false-positive events plus three times the standard deviation in false amplification (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
